  <prompt>
    Add the missing `NodeDestination.Both` enum value to `NodeRoutingConfig.cs:31-64` and extend the JSON converter at `NodeRoutingConfig.cs:247-272` to handle the new value (serialize as `"both"`, deserialize `"both"` → `NodeDestination.Both`). Existing 4 destination values (`Chat`, `Workspace`, `FormPrefill`, `SideEffect`) must remain bit-for-bit unchanged. Implements spec FR-14a.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in C# enums + `System.Text.Json` converters + dispatch-contract evolution.</role>

  <goal>
    `NodeDestination.Both` exists. JSON converter roundtrips `"both"` correctly. Existing 4 values unaffected (unit test verifies). `dotnet build` of `Sprk.Bff.Api` passes. Spec FR-14a acceptance: deserialize-then-serialize roundtrip preserves enum.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14a + design §1.3 (WP3). The Q5 re-shape design promised `chat / workspace / both / side-effect`; code today has Chat/Workspace/FormPrefill/SideEffect. This adds the missing `Both` (used by playbooks that emit BOTH a Workspace tab AND a chat acknowledgment — task 049 wires the handler).
    </background>
